## 2. Architecture Compliance

### 2.1 Layer Adherence

Per CODEBASE_ARCHITECTURE_RULES §2, the database layer follows:

```
Route Handler → Controller → Service → Repository → Prisma Client
```

| Layer | Responsibility | DB Access |
|-------|---------------|-----------|
| Route Handler | HTTP mapping only | ❌ Forbidden |
| Controller | Orchestration | ❌ Forbidden |
| Service | Business logic | ❌ Forbidden |
| Repository | Data access | ✅ Prisma Client |

### 2.2 Prisma as Single Data Access Layer

Per CODEBASE_ARCHITECTURE_RULES §6, all database access goes through:

```
src/lib/db/prisma.ts → Single Prisma Client instance
```

