### 3.3 Partitioned Tables

Prisma does not natively support PostgreSQL table partitioning. The following tables require raw SQL migrations:

| Table | Partition Key | Interval | Notes |
|-------|--------------|----------|-------|
| transactions | created_at | Monthly | High volume |
| messages | created_at | Monthly | High volume |
| notifications | created_at | Monthly | 90-day retention |
| audit_logs | created_at | Monthly | 2-year retention |
| post_analytics | date | Monthly | Aggregate data |
| creator_analytics | date | Monthly | Aggregate data |
| user_activity | created_at | Monthly | 30-day hot data |

**Implementation Approach:**
1. Prisma schema defines the logical structure
2. Initial migration creates base tables
3. Follow-up raw SQL migration converts to partitioned tables
4. Partition automation via pg_partman or cron jobs

### 3.4 Partial Indexes

These require raw SQL (Prisma doesn't support `WHERE` clauses in indexes):

```sql
-- Active subscriptions only
CREATE INDEX idx_subscriptions_active 
  ON subscriptions(user_id, creator_id) 
  WHERE status = 'active';

-- Unread notifications only
CREATE INDEX idx_notifications_unread 
  ON notifications(user_id, created_at DESC) 
  WHERE is_read = false;

-- Published posts only
CREATE INDEX idx_posts_published 
  ON posts(creator_id, published_at DESC) 
  WHERE status = 'published';
```

